  "text": "# Dashboard JSON Schema Version Migration Pipeline\n\n## Overview\nGrafana's dashboard JSON schema version migration pipeline spans both backend (Go) and frontend (TypeScript) implementations. The pipeline transforms dashboards from legacy schema versions to the latest (version 42) through a series of incremental migrations.\n\n## Backend Migration System (Go)\n\n### Migration Runner\nThe migration orchestration happens in `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/migrate.go`, which contains:\n- **`Migrate()` function**: The public API for migrating dashboards to a target schema version\n- **`migrator.migrate()` method**: The internal implementation that:\n  1. Applies frontend defaults (DashboardModel and PanelModel constructor defaults)\n  2. Tracks original transformation and fieldConfig state for accuracy\n  3. Applies panel defaults to all panels (top-level and nested in rows)\n  4. Ensures unique panel IDs\n  5. Executes version-specific migrations sequentially\n  6. Adds built-in annotation queries\n  7. Cleans up the dashboard to match frontend save behavior\n\n### Migration Registry\nThe versioned migration function registry in `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migrations.go` provides:\n- **`GetMigrations(dsInfoProvider)` function**: Returns a `map[int]SchemaVersionMigrationFunc` mapping schema versions (2-42) to their migration functions\n- **`SchemaVersionMigrationFunc` type**: Function signature accepting context and dashboard map\n- **Version range**: MIN_VERSION = 0, LATEST_VERSION = 42\n- Special handling for V33 and V36 which require `DataSourceInfoProvider`\n\n### Individual Migration Steps\nThe `/apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/` directory contains individual migration implementations:\n- **V2.go**: Migrates services.filter structure (time, templating.list)\n- **V3-V35.go**: Various incremental schema transformations\n- **V36.go**: Major datasource reference migration (string names to UID-based objects) with:\n  - `migrateAnnotations()`: Updates annotation datasources\n  - `migrateTemplateVariables()`: Updates variable datasources\n  - `migratePanels()`: Updates panel and target datasources\n- **V37-V42.go**: Modern schema adjustments\n\n### Utility Functions\n- **`datasource_utils.go`**: Datasource migration helpers\n  - `MigrateDatasourceNameToRef()`: Converts string datasource names to structured references\n  - `GetDataSourceRef()`: Creates datasource reference objects\n  - `GetDefaultDSInstanceSettings()`: Retrieves default datasource\n- **`migration_utils.go`**: Shared utility functions\n  - `GetStringValue()`, `GetBoolValue()`, `GetIntValue()`, `GetFloatValue()`: Safe value extraction\n  - `ConvertToFloat()`, `ConvertToInt()`: Type conversion\n- **`frontend_defaults.go`**: Frontend defaults application\n  - `applyFrontendDefaults()`: Applies DashboardModel constructor defaults\n  - `applyPanelDefaults()`: Applies PanelModel constructor defaults\n\n## Frontend Migration System (TypeScript)\n\n### DashboardMigrator Class\nLocated at `public/app/features/dashboard/state/DashboardMigrator.ts`, implements the frontend version migration logic:\n- **`DASHBOARD_SCHEMA_VERSION` constant**: Currently set to 42 (FINAL version for v1 dashboard API)\n- **`constructor(dashboardModel)`**: Initializes with DashboardModel instance\n- **`updateSchema(old, targetSchemaVersion?)` method**: Main migration orchestration that:\n  1. Compares oldVersion with targetVersion\n  2. Executes conditional version-specific migration blocks (v2, v3, v6, v8, etc.)\n  3. Applies panel upgrades to all panels and nested row panels\n  4. Updates schema version after all migrations\n  5. Does NOT add new migrations after v42 (reserved for app platform)\n\n### Key Migration Implementations\n- **Version 2**: Migrates services.filter structure\n- **Version 6**: Converts pulldowns to annotations\n- **Version 16**: Upgrades to grid layout from rows\n- **Version 33**: Converts datasource names to UID-based references\n- **Version 36**: Major datasource reference migration matching backend V36\n  - Updates annotation datasources\n  - Migrates template variable datasources\n  - Handles null datasources by assigning defaults\n  - Processes nested panels in collapsed rows\n  - Migrates target datasources with panel-level inheritance\n- **Version 37-42**: Legend, table display, and field config migrations\n\n### Helper Functions\n- **`migrateDatasourceNameToRef()`**: Converts datasource references, handles null/default cases\n- **`upgradeToGridLayout()`**: Converts legacy row-based layout to grid layout\n- **CloudWatch-specific migrations**: Separate handlers for CloudWatch query and annotation migrations\n\n## Data Flow\n\nThe migration pipeline follows this sequence:\n1. **Frontend requests migration**: DashboardMigrator.updateSchema() is called\n2. **Backend migration**: Optional backend validation/migration via Migrate() function\n3. **Panel upgrades**: Applied uniformly to all panels including nested ones\n4. **Datasource resolution**: Backend uses DataSourceInfoProvider to resolve datasource UIDs\n5. **Defaults application**: Frontend defaults applied before version migrations\n6. **Version increment**: Schema version updated as migrations complete\n\n## Key Design Principles\n\n1. **Version 42 is final**: No new schema migrations allowed for v1 dashboard API (migration to app platform)\n2. **Incremental migrations**: Each version handles one logical change\n3. **Frontend-backend parity**: Backend V36 mirrors frontend V36 implementation\n4. **Datasource abstraction**: DataSourceInfoProvider allows flexible datasource resolution\n5. **Defaults-first approach**: Frontend defaults applied before version migrations to ensure consistency\n6. **Panel ID uniqueness**: Enforced after all migrations to prevent conflicts\n\n## Repository\n- **repo**: grafana/grafana\n- **commit**: 26d36ec\n"
